{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Only require learner drivers to retake the part of a theory test they fail",
        "additional_details": "I want the Government to change this, so if you get over the pass mark on either multiple choice questions or hazard perception but not the other you should only have to redo the one you didn\u2019t get the pass mark for.",
        "background": "It\u2019s annoying when you take your theory test and you pass one section (eg. hazard perception) and fail the other (eg. multiple choice questions) and you have to retake both parts. You shouldn\u2019t have to redo both when you have already passed one section.",
